TY  - JOUR
AU  - Dertwinkel-Kalt, Markus
AU  - Gerhardt, Holger
AU  - Riener, Gerhard
AU  - Schwerter, Frederik
AU  - Strang, Louis
T1  - Concentration Bias in Intertemporal Choice
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdab043
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 89
IS  - 3
SP  - 1314
EP  - 1334
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Many intertemporal trade-offs are unbalanced: while the advantages of options are concentrated in a few periods, the disadvantages are dispersed over numerous periods. We provide novel experimental evidence for “concentration bias,” the tendency to overweight advantages that are concentrated in time. Subjects commit to too much overtime work that is dispersed over multiple days in exchange for a bonus that is concentrated in time: concentration bias increases subjects’ willingness to work by 22.4% beyond what standard discounting models could account for. In additional conditions and a complementary experiment involving monetary payments, we study the mechanisms behind concentration bias and demonstrate the robustness of our findings.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdab043
ER  - 



